    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for the rename feature:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Ollama Model Rename Feature\n\n### Overview\n4 files to modify. No new imports needed anywhere — all required packages (`manifest`, `model`, `os`, `errors`, `io`, `gin`, etc.) are already imported in each file.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go` (after line 765, after `CopyRequest`)\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct — identical shape to `CopyRequest`:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go` (after line 387, between `Copy()` and `Delete()`)\nAdd `Rename()` client method — identical pattern to `Copy()`:\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    if err := c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go`\nAdd `RenameHandler` after line 1483 (after `CopyHandler`). The handler logic:\n1. Bind JSON → **400** on malformed/empty body\n2. Validate + `getExistingName()` for source → **400** on invalid name\n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if not found *(captures `srcManifest` for later deletion — no second lookup needed)*\n4. Validate + `getExistingName()` for destination → **400** on invalid name\n5. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409** if it succeeds (dest exists) *(no writes have happened yet)*\n6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → **500** on failure\n7. `srcManifest.Remove()` + `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` → **500** on failure\n8. **200 OK** (empty body) on success\n\nRegister route on line 1699 after `/api/copy`:\n```go\nr.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)\n```\n\n### Step 4 — `cmd/cmd.go`\n- **`RenameHandler` func** after line 1351 (after `CopyHandler`) — same pattern as `CopyHandler`, prints `\"renamed 'X' to 'Y'\"`\n- **`renameCmd`** after line 2264 (after `deleteCmd`) — `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `checkServerHeartbeat`, `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`\n- **Register `renameCmd`** in both the env-docs loop (~line 2290) and `rootCmd.AddCommand()` (~line 2332), placed after `copyCmd`",
